# .repo-boundary-allow
#
# Path globs that scripts/check-repo-boundaries.sh skips when scanning for
# denylisted strings. These files legitimately *quote* forbidden terms — they
# document the boundary or use a fake credential as a teaching example.
#
# Keep this list short and specific. A new entry means "I have read this file
# and confirmed the match is documentation, not a leak." The denylist policy
# files and the checker script itself are always skipped automatically.
#
# Globs are matched against the repo-relative path (shell `case` semantics).

# Boundary / licensing / security documentation that names the forbidden terms:
docs/architecture/repo-boundaries.md
docs/contributing/license-policy.md
docs/maintainers/review-checklist.md
docs/maintainers/license-review.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
SECURITY.md
docs/pages/security.md

# Teaching example: shows a developer how to mark a project secret as required.
docs-site/guides/environment-variables.md

# The committed env template — safe placeholders only. Exempt from `path:.env.*`.
.env.example
